SUMMARY:Outback Presents Whitney Cummings: The Big Baby Tour
DESCRIPTION:Whitney Cummings is a comedian\, actor\, writer\, producer\, director\, and host of the hit podcast Good for You. Best known for creating and starring in the NBC series Whitney and co-creating the syndicated\, Emmy-nominated CBS comedy 2 Broke Girls\, she has become a leading voice in modern comedy. Cummings has released six stand-up specials\, including Money Shot (2010)\, I Love You (2014)\, I’m Your Girlfriend (2016)\, Can I Touch It? (2019)\, Jokes (2022)\, and her latest\, Mouthy\, which debuted on OnlyFans in November 2023. She has also appeared in numerous television series and films\, such as Good Mourning\, Studio 666\, How It Ends\, and FOX’s Accused\, further solidifying her presence on both the big and small screens.\nBeyond performing\, Cummings is a successful author and filmmaker. In 2017\, she published her memoir\, I’m Fine… And Other Lies\, and made her directorial debut with the feature adaptation of Louann Brizendine’s bestseller\, The Female Brain. She continues to create\, produce\, and perform across platforms\, bringing her sharp humor and fearless perspective to audiences worldwide. She currently lives in Los Angeles.\nPOST-SHOW VIP MEET & GREET ADD-ON\nVIP Ticket to include:\nPost-Show Meet & Greet & Photo with Whitney Cummings.\nMeet & Greet ticket DOES NOT include a seat for the show.\nA separate show ticket MUST be purchased to attend Meet & Greet.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/outback-presents-whitney-cummings-the-big-baby-tour/
LOCATION:Luther Burbank Center for the Arts\, 50 Mark West Springs Road\, Santa Rosa\, CA
CATEGORIES:Comedy
GEO:38.4929;-122.749
